    "caption": "A rainbow lizard with eyes that can look two ways at once.",
    "shortDescription": "Panther chameleons live in the tropical forests of northern and eastern Madagascar, where males can glow in wild reds, greens, blues, and oranges. Each eye can swivel separately, so a chameleon can scan two directions before both eyes lock onto a tiny insect. Fun fact: Its tongue can shoot out to snatch prey while its mitten-like feet and curling tail grip the branch like climbing gear."
